==English==

===Etymology===
# [[wife]] + [[beater]], a man who beats his wife
# The term is said to have taken its name from the Tennessee Williams play "A Streetcar Named Desire," where main character Stanley Kolwalski frequently wore strapless T-shirts as his fashion of choice.

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}
# {{pejorative}} a man who [[frequently]] [[physically]] [[abuses]] his [[wife]].
# {{slang}} a white [[strapless]] [[T-shirt]] worn as the outer [[garment]].

[[ru:wife beater]]